metrics_conclusion: Milkshake has higher complexity than the average song  in terms Chord Complexity.
key_conclusion:
Milkshake is written in the key of C♯ Phrygian.  

According to the Theorytab database, it is the 9th most popular key among Phrygian keys and     the 60th most popular  among all keys. The C♯ Phrygian scale is similar to the C♯ Minor scale except that its 2nd note (D) is a half step lower.  Chord progressions in Phrygian often rely on the major chord built off of this 2nd scale degree (D major) which gives the key its distinctive sound. 

See the C♯ Phrygian Cheat Sheet for popular chords, chord progressions, downloadable midi files and more!

metadata.editComments: Changed it to the actual chorus instead of the verse. The melody barely makes sense to notate with notes though, but this is probably an okay approximation. Also added the chord extensions from the synth line to some of the D chords.

Could be convinced either B or D is the tonic here. They each sound resolved in different bars due to the modal interchange. The pentatonic melody in bar 5 and 6 is in B Minor, but the chords in bar 7 and 8 sounds like they want to resolve to D.
